quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to set the height of the div to 50px, the width to 100px:
[!raw!]
div {
border: none;    
{0}: 100px;
{1}: {2};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]CSS Width and Height[/h1]

To style a [b]<div>[/b] element to have a total width and height of [b]100px[/b]:

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<div>The total width and height of this element is 100px.</div>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css" codeId="541"]div {
   border: 5px solid green;    
   width: 90px;
   height: 90px;
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2621" width="100%"]
[note]The total width and height of the box will be the 90px+5px (border)+5px(border) = 100px;[/note]

[h1]Width and Height Measurement [/h1]

The width and height of an element can be also assigned using [b]percents.[/b] 
In the example below the width of an element is assigned in percentages, the height is in pixels. 

[b]The HTML:[/b][code format="html" ]<div>The total width of this element is <strong>100%</strong> and the total height is <strong>100px</strong> .</div>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css" codeId="542"]div {
   border: 5px solid green;    
   width: [b]100%;[/b]
   height: [b]90px[/b];
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2622" width="100%"]

quizzes.question:
Set the minimum allowable width of the div to 200px:
[!raw!]
div {
{0}: {1};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The Minimum and Maximum Sizes[/h1]

To set the minimum and maximum height and width of an element, you can use the following properties:

[b]min-width[/b] - the minimum width of an element
[b]min-height [/b]- the minimum height of an element
[b]max-width[/b] - the maximum width of an element
[b]max-height [/b]- the maximum height of an element

In the example below, we set the minimum height and maximum width of different paragraphs to 100px. 

[b]The HTML: [/b][code format="html" ]<p class="first">The <strong>minimum height </strong> of this paragraph is set to 100px.</p>
<p class="second">The<strong> maximum width </strong> of this paragraph is set to 100px.</p>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css" codeId="543"]p.first {
   border: 5px solid green;    
   [b]min-height: 100px;[/b]       
}
p.second {
   border: 5px solid green;    
   [b]max-width: 100px;[/b]       
}[/code]
[b]Result: [/b][img id="2623" width="100%"]
